---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="Overview" current="home">
    <div class="page-header">
        <h1>Europe Bikepacking Tour 2026</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">
            Georgia through Turkey, the Balkans, and a counterclockwise lap of
            the Alps. Hardtail, bikepacking bags, dirt roads and singletrack.
            Mid-May to late October.
        </p>
        <div class="meta">
            <span><span class="dot"></span> ~5,500 km</span>
            <span><span class="dot"></span> ~145 days</span>
            <span><span class="dot"></span> ~€4,500</span>
            <span><span class="dot"></span> 9 countries</span>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2>The Route</h2>

    <div class="leg-card">
        <h3>
            <a href={`${base}/legs/1`}>Leg 1 · Georgia — Caucasus Highlights</a>
        </h3>
        <div class="leg-meta">
            <span>~2 weeks</span><span>May 18 – Jun 1</span><span>~500 km</span>
            <span class="tag tag-free">Non-Schengen</span>
        </div>
        <p>
            Tbilisi → Kazbegi → Truso Valley (travertine geology) → Juta Valley
            (Chaukhi Massif) → Shatili (medieval fortress) → Abano Pass →
            Tusheti (Omalo). Stone watchtowers, mineral springs, gorge riding.
            Chaukhi Pass closed in May — route adapted.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="leg-card">
        <h3>
            <a href={`${base}/legs/2`}>Leg 2 · Turkey — Kaçkars & Cappadocia</a>
        </h3>
        <div class="leg-meta">
            <span>~5 weeks</span><span>Jun 1 – Jul 10</span><span
                >~1,000 km + trains</span
            >
            <span class="tag tag-free">Non-Schengen</span>
        </div>
        <p>
            Kaçkar Mountains via yayla roads → train across Anatolia →
            Cappadocia Delight loop → western Turkey → Thrace → Greek border.
            Volcanic geology, fairy chimneys, tea plantations.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="leg-card">
        <h3><a href={`${base}/legs/3`}>Leg 3 · Greece Transit</a></h3>
        <div class="leg-meta">
            <span>3 days</span><span>Jul 12–15</span><span>~350 km</span>
            <span class="tag tag-schengen">3 Schengen days</span>
        </div>
        <p>
            Speed run through Thrace to the Albanian border. Flat, fast,
            functional. Every day costs a Schengen day.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="leg-card">
        <h3>
            <a href={`${base}/legs/4`}>Leg 4 · Albania — Accursed Mountains</a>
        </h3>
        <div class="leg-meta">
            <span>~2 weeks</span><span>Jul 15 – Aug 1</span><span>~500 km</span>
            <span class="tag tag-free">Non-Schengen</span>
        </div>
        <p>
            Shkodër → Theth → Valbona Pass → Lake Koman ferry → northern
            highlands. Karst limestone peaks, turquoise rivers, cheapest country
            on the route.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="leg-card">
        <h3><a href={`${base}/legs/5`}>Leg 5 · Montenegro — Durmitor</a></h3>
        <div class="leg-meta">
            <span>~10 days</span><span>Aug 1–12</span><span>~400 km</span>
            <span class="tag tag-free">Non-Schengen</span>
        </div>
        <p>
            Prokletije → Durmitor National Park → Tara River Canyon → coast at
            Bar. Deepest canyon in Europe, old-growth forests. Ferry to Bari.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="leg-card">
        <h3><a href={`${base}/legs/6`}>Leg 6 · Apennine Highlights</a></h3>
        <div class="leg-meta">
            <span>~12 days</span><span>Aug 13–25</span><span
                >~400 km + trains</span
            >
            <span class="tag tag-schengen">Schengen</span>
        </div>
        <p>
            Train Bari → L'Aquila. The Wolf's Lair loop through Gran Sasso,
            Maiella, and Abruzzo national parks. Campo Imperatore plateau. Train
            to Turin.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="leg-card">
        <h3><a href={`${base}/legs/7`}>Leg 7 · Alps — Piedmont Approach</a></h3>
        <div class="leg-meta">
            <span>4–5 days</span><span>Aug 26–30</span><span>~200 km</span>
            <span class="tag tag-schengen">Schengen</span>
        </div>
        <p>
            Turin east across the Po Plain, cutting into the Venetian Prealps.
            Transition leg — service the bike, rest, arrive at the Dolomites
            fresh.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="leg-card">
        <h3><a href={`${base}/legs/8`}>Leg 8 · Alps — Dolomites</a></h3>
        <div class="leg-meta">
            <span>~10–14 days</span><span>Aug 31 – Sep 13</span><span
                >~500 km</span
            >
            <span class="tag tag-schengen">Schengen</span>
        </div>
        <p>
            Trans-Dolomiti loop from Brixen — WWI military roads, limestone
            towers, enrosadira. Zillertal Trail add-on if conditions allow.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="leg-card">
        <h3>
            <a href={`${base}/legs/9`}>Leg 9 · Alps — Austria & Switzerland</a>
        </h3>
        <div class="leg-meta">
            <span>~10–14 days</span><span>Sep 14–28</span><span>~600 km</span>
            <span class="tag tag-schengen">Schengen</span>
        </div>
        <p>
            Stelvio → Inn Valley → Engadin. Swiss Alpine Bike Route 1 heading
            west. Glacier views, ancient trading passes, impeccable
            infrastructure at Swiss prices.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="leg-card">
        <h3>
            <a href={`${base}/legs/10`}>Leg 10 · Alps — French Alps & Nice</a>
        </h3>
        <div class="leg-meta">
            <span>~10–14 days</span><span>Sep 29 – Oct 10</span><span
                >~400 km</span
            >
            <span class="tag tag-schengen">Schengen</span>
        </div>
        <p>
            Queyras → Mercantour → TNR off-road sections (Assietta, Little Peru,
            Via del Sale) → Nice. The sections worth redoing properly. Decision
            point at Nice.
        </p>
    </div>

    <h2>Schengen Budget</h2>

    <div class="callout callout-warning">
        <div class="callout-title">NZ Bilateral with France</div>
        <p>
            NZ passport holders may get 90 additional days in France after
            Schengen days are used, per a 1947 bilateral agreement. Awaiting
            embassy confirmation. Clear departure point: Nice. If bilateral
            works → keep riding in France. If not → fly to NZ.
        </p>
    </div>

    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Action</th>
                <th>Schengen days used</th>
                <th>Running total</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>France (Jan 16 – Apr 7)</td><td>82</td><td>82</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Denmark (May 8 - May 10)</td><td>3</td><td>85</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Greece transit (~Jul 15–18)</td><td>3</td><td>88</td></tr>
            <tr
                ><td><em>Gap: Jul 18 – Sep 5 (non-Schengen)</em></td><td>—</td
                ><td>—</td></tr
            >
            <tr
                ><td>Italy entry ~Sep 5</td><td>Available: ~55 days</td><td
                    >—</td
                ></tr
            >
            <tr
                ><td>Alps loop (Sep 5 – ~Oct 20)</td><td>~45</td><td
                    >45 in current window</td
                ></tr
            >
            <tr
                ><td><strong>Buffer remaining</strong></td><td
                    ><strong>~5 days</strong></td
                ><td>—</td></tr
            >
        </tbody>
    </table>
    <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
        By Oct 4, all France days fall outside the 180-day window → nearly full
        90-day reset. Loop is comfortable.
    </p>

    <h2>Budget</h2>

    <table>
        <thead>
            <tr><th>Country</th><th>€/day</th><th>Days</th><th>Total</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            <tr><td>Georgia</td><td>12</td><td>14</td><td>€170</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Turkey</td><td>12</td><td>40</td><td>€480</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Greece</td><td>22</td><td>3</td><td>€65</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Albania</td><td>12</td><td>17</td><td>€200</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Montenegro</td><td>18</td><td>12</td><td>€215</td></tr>
            <tr
                ><td>Italy (Apennines + Dolomites)</td><td>24</td><td>26</td><td
                    >€615</td
                ></tr
            >
            <tr><td>Austria</td><td>25</td><td>7</td><td>€175</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Switzerland</td><td>35</td><td>12</td><td>€420</td></tr>
            <tr><td>France (Alps)</td><td>22</td><td>14</td><td>€310</td></tr>
            <tr
                ><td colspan="3"><strong>Living subtotal</strong></td><td
                    ><strong>€2,650</strong></td
                ></tr
            >
            <tr><td colspan="3">Flights, trains, ferries</td><td>€1,550</td></tr
            >
            <tr><td colspan="3">Bike maintenance & spares</td><td>€250</td></tr>
            <tr
                ><td colspan="3"><strong>Grand total</strong></td><td
                    ><strong>~€4,450</strong></td
                ></tr
            >
        </tbody>
    </table>
</Layout>
